  "text": "area of 1.29 ha (range 0.019-7.569 ha). We measured isolation as the shortest straight-line distance from a kipuka to the nearest large tract of continuous sagebrush steppe outside of the lava flow (i.e., the sagebrush-steppe ''mainland''). Because of difficulty discriminating sagebrush steppe on digital orthophoto quarter-quadrangles in the Rockland Valley, we used ArcInfo (ESRI) to identify regions of sagebrush cover . 10 ha on the Idaho Gap Analysis land cover classification map [CITATION_1] and measured the isolation of agricultural patches as the distance between the agricultural patch and the nearest area of sagebrush steppe .10 ha.",
